			"note": "QUESTIONS:<div><br></div><div>- How big of a system can a computer reasonably solve in \"a minute\"?</div><div>- How can you ask a computer to do this sort of problem?</div><div>- How can you get a sense of what to expect? &nbsp;When I use a computer to solve problems like this, I know a lot about what should happen from the get go. &nbsp;I know all kinds of internal consistency checks. &nbsp;These come from careful hand calculations and good understanding of theory. &nbsp; What sort of theory does it makes sense to ask about?</div><div>- How do computers actually solve such systems?&nbsp;</div><div>- What about allowing the coefficients to be other sorts of numbers? &nbsp;(E.g., complex numbers, elements of a finite field?)&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>"
